<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--@import "_head.kit"-->

<body>
    <!--@import "_header.kit"-->

    <main>
        <section class="hero section-fade">
            <div class="container hero-grid">
                <div class="hero-copy">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio / Web Design / Front-End</p>
                    <h1>Pedro Porto Borges designs and builds clean digital experiences.</h1>
                    <p class="lead">This portfolio is a light, editorial home for selected projects, process notes, and practical web experiments. Replace this introduction with your real story when you are ready.</p>
                    <div class="button-row">
                        <a href="/portfolio.html" class="btn btn-primary">View projects</a>
                        <a href="/contact.html" class="btn btn-secondary">Contact me</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-card" aria-label="Abstract portfolio preview">
                    <div class="orbit orbit-one"></div>
                    <div class="orbit orbit-two"></div>
                    <div class="preview-panel">
                        <span>Selected Work</span>
                        <strong>04</strong>
                    </div>
                    <div class="preview-stack">
                        <span></span>
                        <span></span>
                        <span></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="intro-section">
            <div class="container split-section">
                <div>
                    <p class="eyebrow">Introduction</p>
                    <h2>A portfolio shaped for clarity, calm browsing, and fast content updates.</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="intro-copy">
                    <p>Use this space to describe who you are, what you study or build, and the kind of work you want people to notice first.</p>
                    <p>The structure is intentionally simple: a homepage introduction, a portfolio index, project detail pages, and a contact page with social links.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="featured-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="section-heading">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Featured Projects</p>
                    <h2>Recent work</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="project-grid">
                    <article class="project-card">
                        <a href="/project-1.html" class="project-cover project-cover-one" aria-label="Open Project One"></a>
                        <div class="project-card-body">
                            <p class="project-meta">Web Design / 2026</p>
                            <h3><a href="/project-1.html">Project One</a></h3>
                            <p>A concise placeholder for the first project, ready for your real description and screenshots.</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                    <article class="project-card">
                        <a href="/project-2.html" class="project-cover project-cover-two" aria-label="Open Project Two"></a>
                        <div class="project-card-body">
                            <p class="project-meta">Interface / 2026</p>
                            <h3><a href="/project-2.html">Project Two</a></h3>
                            <p>A clean project card for an app, website, or class assignment with a dedicated detail page.</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                </div>
                <div class="section-action">
                    <a href="/portfolio.html" class="text-link">See all projects</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <!--@import "_footer.kit"-->
</body>

</html>
